Running `podman unshare --rootless-netns iptables -S`, i get this:
```
❯ podman unshare --rootless-netns iptables -S
-P INPUT ACCEPT
-P FORWARD ACCEPT
-P OUTPUT ACCEPT
-N NETAVARK_FORWARD
-N NETAVARK_INPUT
-N NETAVARK_ISOLATION_1
-N NETAVARK_ISOLATION_2
-N NETAVARK_ISOLATION_3
-A INPUT -m comment --comment "netavark firewall rules" -j NETAVARK_INPUT
-A FORWARD -j NETAVARK_ISOLATION_1
-A FORWARD -m comment --comment "netavark firewall rules" -j NETAVARK_FORWARD
-A NETAVARK_FORWARD -m conntrack --ctstate INVALID -j DROP
-A NETAVARK_FORWARD -d 10.89.0.0/24 -m conntrack --ctstate RELATED,ESTABLISHED -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_FORWARD -s 10.89.0.0/24 -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_FORWARD -d 10.89.1.0/24 -m conntrack --ctstate RELATED,ESTABLISHED -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_FORWARD -s 10.89.1.0/24 -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_INPUT -s 10.89.0.0/24 -p udp -m udp --dport 1153 -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_INPUT -s 10.89.0.0/24 -p tcp -m tcp --dport 1153 -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_INPUT -s 10.89.1.0/24 -p udp -m udp --dport 1153 -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_INPUT -s 10.89.1.0/24 -p tcp -m tcp --dport 1153 -j ACCEPT
-A NETAVARK_ISOLATION_1 -i podman2 ! -o podman2 -j NETAVARK_ISOLATION_2
-A NETAVARK_ISOLATION_2 -o podman2 -j DROP
-A NETAVARK_ISOLATION_3 -j NETAVARK_ISOLATION_2
```

Can confirm, with `firewall_driver=nftables`, it works as expected.

If some Nix users come across this, you have to provide `nftables` as an `extraPackage` as its not included by default:
```
pkgs.podman.override {
  extraPackages = [pkgs.nftables];
};
```
